 The spiral is the usual Ulam (counter‑clockwise) spiral.  

For a cell that sits just after a corner of a new layer, let  

\[
m=\max(|x|,|y|)
\]

be the “layer number”.  
For the number \(N=2026\) we have  

\[
(2\cdot22+1)^{2}=45^{2}=2025<2026\le (2\cdot23+1)^{2}=47^{2}=2209,
\]

so \(m=23\) and \(2026\) is the first cell of layer 23, located at \((23,-(23-1))=(23,-22)\).

The eight neighbours of \((23,-22)\) are  

\[
\begin{array}{ccl}
(22,-22) &\;&2025\\
(22,-21) &\;&1850\\
(23,-21) &\;&2027\\
(24,-21) &\;&2212\\
(24,-22) &\;&2211\\
(24,-23) &\;&2210\\
(23,-23) &\;&2209\\
(22,-23) &\;&2208
\end{array}
\]

(These are obtained from the formulas for the numbers on the right–hand, top, left and bottom sides of a layer.)

Adding them

\[
2025+1850+2027+2212+2211+2210+2209+2208
=16952 .
\]

Hence the sum of all eight neighbours of \(2026\) is  

\[
\boxed{16952}.
\]
----
